canonical:
  title: 晝景
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 天際彤雲晝不收寒溪無響草莖柔人間六月多忙熱誰信山中枕碧流
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 晝景
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 天際彤雲晝不收。寒溪無響草莖柔。人間六月多忙熱。誰信山中枕碧流。
korean:
  title: 주경
  author: 김시습
  language: kor
  text: |-
    하늘 끝의 붉은 구름이 낮에도 걷치지 않는데
    찬 시내는 소리 없고 풀줄기는 부드럽다
    인간의 6월은 번잡한 더위가 많거니
    누가 이 산중의 푸른 물을 베개할 줄 알리
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0640&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Daylight Scene
  author: Kim Si-seup
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Red clouds at heaven's edge linger through the day, unwilling to disperse.
    The cold stream runs silent, its grass stems tender and supple.
    In the human world, June brings only bustling heat and toil—
    who would believe that here in the mountains, we pillow our heads on emerald waters?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'red clouds' (彤雲) evoke both visual beauty and a sense of lingering melancholy, refusing to clear even in daylight
  - key: ''
    value: The contrast between the chaotic, sweltering world below and the serene mountain sanctuary reflects a classic Korean literati theme of retreat and spiritual freedom
